Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy
of this dataset and associated documentation files (the "Dataset"), to use
the Dataset for academic research and educational purposes, subject to the
following conditions:

1. ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENT
   Any use of this Dataset in research, publications, presentations, or
   derivative works must include the following citation:

   Khanna, Mridul (2025). "IUPMS-CZ-IRS Merged Panel Dataset:
   A Comprehensive US Commuting Zone Panel (1980-2023)."
   Heidelberg University. https://github.com/Mridlll/Environmental-OGS

2. PERMITTED USES
   - Academic research and scholarly analysis
   - Educational purposes in university courses
   - Non-commercial research by governmental or non-profit organizations
   - Replication of published research results
   - Creation of derivative datasets with proper attribution

3. RESTRICTED USES
   - Commercial use requires written permission from the author
   - Redistribution must include this license and citation information
   - Cannot claim original authorship of the Dataset

4. DERIVATIVE WORKS
   If you create derivative datasets or substantially modify this Dataset:
   - You must clearly acknowledge this Dataset as the source
   - You must document all modifications made
   - You should share derivative datasets under similar terms (encouraged but not required)

5. NO WARRANTY
   THE DATASET IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
   IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,
   FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL
   THE AUTHOR BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES, OR OTHER LIABILITY ARISING
   FROM THE USE OF THE DATASET.

6. SOURCE DATA
   This Dataset integrates public domain data from US government agencies:
   - Internal Revenue Service (IRS) Statistics of Income
   - Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) Air Quality System
   - US Census Bureau (Decennial Census, American Community Survey)
   - Bureau of Labor Statistics (County Business Patterns, QCEW)

   All source data is in the public domain as works of the US government.
   The compilation, cleaning, merging, and documentation represent the
   original contribution of this Dataset.

7. FEEDBACK AND COLLABORATION
   Users are encouraged to:
   - Report data quality issues via GitHub issues
   - Share improvements and corrections with the community
   - Collaborate on extensions and updates to the Dataset

